<subSubSection id="C30F0386B137FF92FF55FE50FC65FBB6" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB137FF92FF55FE50FEC8FDD7" blockId="2.[166,1225,436,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
D i a g n o s i s. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FD83FE50FD02FE76" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[525,644,437,462]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FD83FE50FD02FE76" box="[525,644,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized from the other Old World Pyrgotini by the following combination of characters: prosternum bearing a pair of nipple- or finger-like lobes, femora apico-ventrally with postero- and antero-ventral row of thickened setae (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FEE4FDF1FE20FD97" box="[362,422,532,559]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">fig. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FE3DFDF1FE5BFD97" box="[435,477,532,559]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FE3DFDF1FE45FD96" box="[435,451,532,558]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FE41FDF0FE5BFD97" box="[463,477,533,559]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[166,199,1721,1743]" captionTargetBox="[190,1222,602,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[166,1231,602,1679]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 7. Eupyrgota vespiformis, ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–4 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — left anterior; 4 — dorsal); 5 — wing; 6–7 — abdomen (6 — left; 7— dorsal)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403947/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">7</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
; 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FE65FDF0FE7CFD97" box="[491,506,533,559]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[166,199,1588,1610]" captionTargetBox="[241,1189,195,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-8@16.[240,1189,195,1510]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Eupyrgota flaviseta, holotype ♀ (1–6), paratypes ♀ (7–9) and} (10–14) (USNM): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — dorsal); 5 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 6 — mid femur, anterior view; 7 — epandrium, right; 8–9 — phallus glans, right and ventral; 10 — abdomen, dorsal; 11 — same, ventral, macerated in KOH; 12 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 13 — aculeus, ventral; 14 — spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403949/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">8</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FD89FDF0FDB7FD96" box="[519,561,532,559]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FD89FDF0FD91FD97" box="[519,535,533,559]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FDADFDF1FDB7FD96" box="[547,561,532,558]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">6</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
) and except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FD69FDF0FC5BFD97" authority="(Aldrich)" baseAuthorityName="Aldrich" box="[743,989,532,559]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviseta">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FD69FDF0FCE3FD96" box="[743,869,532,558]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">E. flaviseta</emphasis>
(Aldrich)
</taxonomicName>
, the oviscape with a pair of heavily sclerotized hooks at the apico-ventral margin (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB137FF92FC23FDD0FBFAFDF7" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[941,1148,564,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" pagination="3 - 25" refId="ref10626" refString="Korneyev, V. A. A revision of Afrotropical species of the Eupyrgota (Diptera, Pyrgotidae): the spinifemur group and latipennis subgroup of species // Vestnik zoologii. - 2006 a. - 40, N 1. - P. 3 - 25." type="book chapter" year="2006">Korneyev, 2006 a</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FB06FDD1FB42FDF7" box="[1160,1220,564,591]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[166,199,1357,1379]" captionTargetBox="[196,1203,181,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[196,1203,174,1356]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig.2. Eupyrgota alienata, holotype ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) and non-type ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — wing; 6 — fore coxa. Рис. 2. Eupyrgota alienata, голотип ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) и нетиповая ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — крыло; 6 — передний тазик." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403935/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FF28FDB0FF32FDD7" box="[166,180,597,623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" captionTargetBox="[263,1145,180,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-5@9.[191,1208,174,1626]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Eupyrgota armipes, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — fore trochanter; 9 — mid trochanter; 10 — wing; 11 — mesonotum and abdomen, dorsally; 12 — abdomen, posterior." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FF28FDB0FF32FDD7" box="[166,180,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FF4CFDB1FF6BFDD7" box="[194,237,596,623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
5, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FF53FDB0FF6BFDD7" box="[221,237,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FF77FDB1FE81FDD6" box="[249,263,596,622]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">6</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FE9AFDB0FEA5FDD7" box="[276,291,597,623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[166,199,1588,1610]" captionTargetBox="[241,1189,195,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-8@16.[240,1189,195,1510]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Eupyrgota flaviseta, holotype ♀ (1–6), paratypes ♀ (7–9) and} (10–14) (USNM): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — dorsal); 5 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 6 — mid femur, anterior view; 7 — epandrium, right; 8–9 — phallus glans, right and ventral; 10 — abdomen, dorsal; 11 — same, ventral, macerated in KOH; 12 — oviscape apex, ventrally; 13 — aculeus, ventral; 14 — spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403949/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B137FF92FEA1FDB0FEBBFDD7" box="[303,317,597,623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[166,199,1357,1379]" captionTargetBox="[196,1203,181,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[196,1203,174,1356]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig.2. Eupyrgota alienata, holotype ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) and non-type ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — wing; 6 — fore coxa. Рис. 2. Eupyrgota alienata, голотип ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) и нетиповая ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — крыло; 6 — передний тазик." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403935/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FEA1FDB0FEBBFDD7" box="[303,317,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB137FF92FF55FD90FB98FD16" blockId="2.[166,1225,436,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
Presence of the nipple-like lobes on the prosternum is a unique character of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FBC4FD90FB47FD36" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[1098,1217,629,654]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FBC4FD90FB47FD36" box="[1098,1217,629,654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which does not occur in other pyrgotid genera and supports its monophyly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB137FF92FF55FD51FC65FBB6" blockId="2.[166,1225,436,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
The rows of spurious setae on the femora are known also in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FC19FD51FB42FD77" authority="Wulp (Pyrgotini)" box="[919,1220,692,719]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Euphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FC19FD51FC76FD76" box="[919,1008,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Euphya</emphasis>
Wulp (Pyrgotini)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FF28FD30FE7FFD57" authority="Paramonov (Toxurini)" authorityName="Paramonov (Toxurini" authorityYear="1958" box="[166,505,724,751]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Epice" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FF28FD30FF62FD56" box="[166,228,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Epice</emphasis>
Paramonov (Toxurini)
</taxonomicName>
and numerous taxa in the families 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FC15FD31FBB5FD56" box="[923,1075,724,750]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Richardiidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FBB1FD31FB4FFD56" authorityName="E.Newman" authorityYear="1834" box="[1087,1225,724,750]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tephritidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FF53FD11FE1BFCB6" box="[221,413,756,782]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Platystomatidae</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, in a few 
<collectingRegion id="49D19EEFB137FF92FD4CFD11FCA2FCB6" box="[706,804,756,782]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Oriental</collectingRegion>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FC20FD10FBA3FCB6" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[942,1061,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FC20FD10FBA3FCB6" box="[942,1061,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the spur-like setae are poorly expressed. Species of both 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FD38FCF1FC89FC96" box="[694,783,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Euphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FD38FCF1FC89FC96" box="[694,783,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Euphya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FCDEFCF0FC08FC96" authorityName="Paramonov (Toxurini" authorityYear="1958" box="[848,910,789,814]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Epice" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FCDEFCF0FC08FC96" box="[848,910,789,814]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Epice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the saddle-like shape of the prosternum without prominent lobes and the oviscape without hook-like lobes. Females of the East Asian (Palaearctic and 
<collectingRegion id="49D19EEFB137FF92FC0BFCB1FC6CFCD7" box="[901,1002,852,879]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Oriental</collectingRegion>
) species 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FBD4FCB1FE2FFC36" authority="Hendel" authorityName="Hendel" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtoscutellata">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FBD4FCB1FECAFC36" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Adapsilia hirtoscutellata</emphasis>
Hendel
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FE6AFC90FD40FC36" authority="Chen" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[484,710,884,911]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myopoides">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FE6AFC90FDF9FC36" box="[484,639,884,911]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">A. myopoides</emphasis>
Chen
</taxonomicName>
both possess similarly sclerotized hook-like lobes on the oviscape, but they are located in a different position and are separated by a small sclerotized ventro-medial lobe or sclerite (
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB137FF92FC8DFC50FC45FC77" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[771,963,949,975]" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" pagination="19 - 46" refId="ref10584" refString="Korneyev, V. A. Genera of Palaearctic Pyrgotidae (Diptera, Acalyptrata), with nomenclatural notes and a key // Vestnik zoologii. - 2004. - 38, N 1. - P. 19 - 46." type="journal article" year="2004">Korneyev, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB137FF92FC5FFC51FF64FC57" author="Nartshuk, E. P. &amp; Korneyev, V. A." pageId="2" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref10772" refString="Nartshuk, E. P., Korneyev, V. A. Data on the fauna of Pyrgotidae (Diptera, Cyclorrhapha) of the Russian Far East // Far East Entomologist. - 2005. - 147. - P. 1 - 10." type="book chapter" year="2005">Nartshuk, Korneyev, 2005</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 13, 14). These species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FCFDFC30FC6CFC56" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[883,1002,981,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FCFDFC30FC6CFC56" box="[883,1002,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of nipple-like lobes on the prosternum and spur-like setae on the femora.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F0386B137FF93FF55FBF0FCCAFF51" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB137FF93FF55FBF0FCCAFF51" blockId="2.[166,1225,436,1839]" lastBlockId="3.[174,1233,175,746]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Moderate or large (wing length 7.0–21.0 mm) wasp-like flies, often with petiolate abdomen, yellow and brown coloration of body and wings with darkened band or brown spots on anterior half or also at middle. Head normally higher than wide, short or moderately long setose; ocelli absent; parafacial microsetulose, with subocular dilation; facial carina developed or absent; epistoma (= “supraclypeal sclerite” of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB137FF92FBDEFB70FF67FB77" author="Korneyev, V. A." pageId="2" pageNumber="113" pagination="19 - 46" refId="ref10584" refString="Korneyev, V. A. Genera of Palaearctic Pyrgotidae (Diptera, Acalyptrata), with nomenclatural notes and a key // Vestnik zoologii. - 2004. - 38, N 1. - P. 19 - 46." type="journal article" year="2004">Korneyev, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB137FF92FF65FB51FEB0FB77" author="Korneyev, V. A." box="[235,310,1204,1231]" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" pagination="3 - 25" refId="ref10626" refString="Korneyev, V. A. A revision of Afrotropical species of the Eupyrgota (Diptera, Pyrgotidae): the spinifemur group and latipennis subgroup of species // Vestnik zoologii. - 2006 a. - 40, N 1. - P. 3 - 25." type="book chapter" year="2006">2006 a</bibRefCitation>
) low to moderately high (at most 0.33 times as high as face); lateral vertical seta short or indistinguishable; antenna as long as face, flagellomere 1 almost as long as pedicel; palpus usually as long as flagellomere 1 (or slightly longer in some 
<collectingRegion id="49D19EEFB137FF92FC79FB11FBDFFAB6" box="[1015,1113,1268,1294]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">Oriental</collectingRegion>
species), parallel-sided or apically expanded; labellum large, fleshy; prosternum bearing a pair of finger- or nipple-like ventral lobes; presutural supra-alar and prescutellar acrostichal setae absent; scutellum with 1–5 pairs of setae; wing with humeral and subcostal breaks present; costa reaching medial vein; Sc straight, narrowly broken before costa; R 
<subScript id="17915248B137FF92FC64FA62FB83FA2D" attach="left" box="[1002,1029,1415,1429]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">2+3</subScript>
strongly curved, always with spurious vein joined to angulate break of R 
<subScript id="17915248B137FF92FCCAFA42FCD9FA0D" attach="left" box="[836,863,1447,1461]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">2+3</subScript>
; Cu 
<subScript id="17915248B137FF92FC1CFA42FC1CFA0D" attach="left" box="[914,922,1447,1461]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">2</subScript>
short; halter yellow; mid coxa anteroventrally setose and setulose but without “brush” or “comb” of setae; hind coxa anteroventrally without “brush” of setae; fore and mid trochanters without or with “brushes” of short spine-like or hook-like setae; femora ventrally with 2 rows of thickened, usually spine-like setae; female mid femur either with bare membranous femoral organ of various position, or lacking it entirely; hind tarsi in both sexes asymmetrical, with brushes of dense setulae on medial surfaces of tarsomeres; syntergite 1 + 
<quantity id="4CEDFDE8B137FF92FC2FF9B0FC48F9D6" box="[929,974,1620,1647]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
both sexes narrowed at middle; female with rather short, ventrally curved oviscape (not longer than remaining abdomen), bearing 2 sclerotized hook-like projections ventro-apically (except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB137FF92FBC2F970FE8DF977" authority="Malloch" authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviseta">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB137FF92FBC2F970FB4FF916" box="[1100,1225,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="113">E. flaviseta</emphasis>
Malloch
</taxonomicName>
), but without spinules or taenia-like sclerites on eversible membrane; aculeus short, flattened dorso-ventrally, with wide, bulky base and narrow stiletto-like apex; 3 oval, smooth spermathecae; in male, hypandrium narrow, with microtrichose flap-like phallic guide; phallapodeme very narrow, vanes separate, joined to hypandrium rather than to bar- like gonites; ejaculatory apodeme fan-shaped; phallus without large sclerites of acrophallus, with paired, sometimes loop-like sclerites of praeputium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F0386B136FF93FF6DFF15FE24FEF2" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB136FF93FF6DFF15FE24FEF2" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FDBBFF15FD2AFEB1" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[565,684,240,265]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FDBBFF15FD2AFEB1" box="[565,684,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur predominantly in the 
<collectingRegion id="49D19EEFB136FF93FB84FF0AFB4AFEB1" box="[1034,1228,239,265]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Oriental Region</collectingRegion>
, with a few representatives also in the Palaearctic, Afrotropical, and Australasian Regions (Papuan Subregion).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F0386B136FF93FF6DFEB5FC36FD52" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB136FF93FF6DFEB5FCA9FD12" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
T a x o n o m y. In this and a forthcoming paper (Korneyev, in press), 38 species are considered to belong in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FE5AFE95FDCDFE31" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[468,587,368,393]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FE5AFE95FDCDFE31" box="[468,587,368,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<quantity id="4CEDFDE8B136FF93FDD5FE8AFD1FFE31" box="[603,665,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" unit="in" value="25.0">25 in</quantity>
the nominative subgenus, and 
<quantity id="4CEDFDE8B136FF93FB9BFE8AFBD4FE31" box="[1045,1106,367,393]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" unit="in" value="13.0">13 in</quantity>
two other subgenera; three species (
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FE6DFE75FCE5FE11" authority="Hendel, 1914" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" box="[483,867,399,426]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Apyrgota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubiseta">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FE6DFE75FD3CFE11" box="[483,698,399,426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Apyrgota pubiseta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB136FF93FD4AFE6AFCE5FE11" author="Hendel, F." box="[708,867,399,425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" pagination="77 - 117" refId="ref10493" refString="Hendel, F. Neue Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Pyrgotinen // Archiv fur Naturgeschichte. - 1914 (1913). - 79 A, N 11. - S. 77 - 117 + 1 Taf." type="book chapter" year="1914">Hendel, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from (?) 
<collectingCountry id="F302109DB136FF93FC52FE6AFB9AFE11" box="[988,1052,399,425]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">India</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FBECFE6AFE61FE71" authority="Bezzi, 1929" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illingworthana">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FBECFE6AFEDFFE71" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Adapsilia illingworthana</emphasis>
Bezzi, 1929
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FDABFE4AFC54FE72" authority="Paramonov, 1958" authorityName="Paramonov" authorityYear="1958" box="[549,978,431,458]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gratiosa">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FDABFE4AFD7FFE71" box="[549,761,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Adapsilia gratiosa</emphasis>
Paramonov, 1958
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F302109DB136FF93FB90FE4AFB0AFE72" box="[1054,1164,431,458]" name="Australia" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Australia</collectingCountry>
) possibly belong elsewhere. Some nominal species are possible synonyms of the others; several undescribed new species are recognized in collections. In total, the genus is believed to include 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FE80FDF5FE9FFD91" box="[270,281,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">c</emphasis>
. 40–45 species, and needs a detailed revision for the Oriental and Australasian species. This, however, is out of the scope of the present work, and I only consider here the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FEABFDB5FE1AFDD1" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[293,412,592,617]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FEABFDB5FE1AFDD1" box="[293,412,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
needing formal taxonomic actions (new combinations for transferred species, some new synonymies, new taxa, and a revised rank). A key to the subgenera will be published in the second part of this series of papers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB136FF93FF6DFD55FC36FD52" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
I therefore transfer the 
<typeStatus id="54AEEEAFB136FF93FE78FD55FDAEFD72" box="[502,552,688,714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">type</typeStatus>
species of 
